@poosmate There needs to be a temperature differential between the two metals for a voltage to be generated.
This is how a thermocouple works. The voltage generated is directly related to the temperature differential. 
If you reverse this you get the Peltier effect. That is, if you apply a voltage across two different metals, you obtain a temperature differential. The peltier effect can then be used as a heating or cooling device depending on which metal you connect to

